HEADWORD: orthogamy
<hw>or*thog"a*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ortho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ marriage.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Direct fertilization in plants, as when the pollen fertilizing the
ovules comes from the stamens of the same blossom; -- opposed to
<contr>heterogamy</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orthognathic</ent>⟦br⟧
